flavorText.string(): People would kill for what I've got.
The Ethereal Crisis began with a destructive storm of Ethereum crystals.
A tranquil wood dotted with Ethereum crystals.
All of the world's knowledge. The hard part is understanding it.
Bits of coin. They're not much now. Used to buy empires though.
Death doesn't stop curiosity.
The library attracted many unwanted visitors.
The spiderlings preyed on those who would trespass in the library.
Crystal shards from the plains of Ethereum.
Sometimes to understand is to read beyond the words.
This is a small Merkle Tree. Legend says that these trees make up the backbone of our Universe.
Searching for knowledge has its risks.
Keeper of the ancient texts.
The keeper had been a fixture of the library since time immemorial.
How many kingdoms pillaged? All for a few books.
The first currencies used by the ancient races.
Dark secrets often require dark sacrifices.
A single text might feed a family for generations.
The spiderlings were loyal friends to the undead scholars.
Still brimming with power after all these millenia.
Secrets learned and forgotten. This is the fate of all knowledge.
Tracing the ever-linking branches allows for divination of the past and the future.
An ancient statue brought to life with ethereal energy.
The librarian has served his post at least since the invention of writing.
As many arms as books. As many eyes as man.
"One might spend a lifetime on one text. I know I have."-Matthias the Learned
The ancient coins came in many denominations like silver and gold.
All things through the study of Ethereum.
A single text might curse a family for generations.
The venom takes days to kill.
How many souls have been trapped within?
How many lives had been sacrificed for this one page?
Most empires have schools dedicated to the divinations of the Merkle Trees.
The creature was made from the same ancient stone as the library itself.
All attempts to interfere with the librarian have been met with deadly response.
A statue used for ceremonial offerings to the god of Knowledge and Preservation.
"I rarely get to read for pleasure anymore."- anonymous librarian
We as a community should move away from coins like these.
This experiment killed everyone involved.
"We have a 97% retention rate."-Ekhart the statistician
They're also used for transportation.
"To the moon!"-ancient proverb
"These ancient fonts are all just scribbles to me."-Erpy the librarian
"Maybe in our world there lives a happy little tree over there"-Bob Ross
We know from ancient records that his name is Mortimer.
The ancient peoples called him 'orac zibl', meaning 'abnormally armed.'
Did you try turning it off and on again?
"Steal from the rich, give to the rich."-Library Thief, A Memoir
They've crawled the whole library, so they're a pretty good search engine.
What's the point of all that knowledge without some application?
Happy's monster drawings are adored by collectors. Not so much by adventurers.
Cursed crystals drawn in Happy's signature style.
A newly grown Merkle Tree.
A poisonous mushroom drawn in a friendly style.
Merkle Trees are common in Happy's Forest.
White Baneberry
A leaf used for filtering noxious swamp gases.
A harmless looking bean used to produce ricin
Happy's things. Or at least how Happy imagines her things.
A table full of ingredients for a helpful Happy potion.
He called out from the trees. The words were branches and blades.
They're not so happy looking when they're eating your livestock.
Ethereum crystals can build and burn empires. Happy only drew the bad kind.
Altering the limbs can subtly alter current events.
Happy makes an excellent stew with these.
Happy is a diviner of the ancient trees. She bends their branches to alter the fates of travelers.
Happy preferred the eyes of real children.
One of the few surviving Happy illustrations featuring a non-deadly plant.
A single thorn can kill an ox!
Happy keeps a very well organized shop
Happy only brews the helpful potions for herself.
Happy made a horrible pact. She gave her soul to save her forest.
Dionaea muscipula have been known to swallow small armies.
Happy offered the pretty crystals to local villagers.
Who could resist an offer to change one's past?
Amanita are best known for nibbling at traveler's ankles.
Happy hangs the souls of lost travelers in her trees to light the forest at night.
Doll's eyes are known for whispering insults at passersby.
Andraeanum leaves possess sufficient intelligence for writing above-average poetry.
The thorny beans are often found rolling along the forest floor in search of prey.
Happy is very early to rise and enjoys watching sunrises.
Happy was once a master potion maker before the corruption set in.
A wooden totem holding the essence of the forest. Happy's only friend.
In real life they have glowing mouths due to selective uptake of radioactive ground soil.
"They're an investment, really."-US Government
The banner of House Merkle
Forest nymphs who fail their tribe are said to reincarnate as Amanita.
"They don't look anything like this really."- Skeleton King's Gardener
If you knock them off they roll after you and call you names. It's hurtful.
Unlike Doll's Eyes
column16: andraeanum may offer words of advice to weary pilgrims.

flavorText.string(): "Rice 'n beans?"-Jesse
That bag has an animal head in it.
Happy painted this still-life as a gift to a good friend.
Muscipula make gobbling sounds that are often mistaken for the calls of wild turkeys.
These seem pretty portable. Are they considered a light node?
"Draw me a data structure"-Patrick
"The stew is really good trust me bro"-Happy
A local punishment involves being locked in a room with a bag of Doll's Eyes.
"Watch out for that crazy lady"-Anthurium Andraeanum
They explode like poisonous grenades when thrown.
Happy paints her nails every weekend with fresh animal blood.
Happy graduated from the Royal Arts Academy of Elias with a degree in Alchemy.
"Always recycle!"-Moose Head
Guardians of the ancient crystals.
Show me your dead. I would speak with them.
An ancient Ethereum crystal fallen to ground.
A common infantryman of the Ethereal Wastes.
Even the great city of Elias was once a hamlet.
Fallen crystals are not always a boon to young empires.
A warrior from the frozen city of Elias.
Outcast magicians can often find mercenary work.
Even nature can succumb to the power of fallen crystals.
A tranquil wood dotted with Ethereum crystals.
A small stone carving of the City of Elias.
When we perish, the crystal will be yours. Not a day before.
He gives the gift of life. He gives of himself.
I was lost when I first laid eyes on the magnificent stone. Lost and mad and dying.
"My soldiers have agile hearts and agile minds."-Lady of Wealth
Early civilizations were often built around fallen crystals.
The Ethereal Crisis began with a destructive storm of Ethereum crystals.
The clans of Elias fight in an endless brawl for control of the city.
Shall I end you with my staff or my sword?
"I guard my treasure with rivers of flame."-Lady of Fire
The Lady of the Forest hides her power here.
These totems are sold to tourists in the city of Elias.
Twinkling in the tempest. The foundations of power.
Rise up and be alive again. Time is short, both yours and mine.
I camped at the crystal's base. I awoke in a storm of bones.
Fencers are taught to mimic the fighting styles of sand scorpions.
Light and warmth even through the coldest winters.
"This age will come to an end. The wizards have seen to that."-Lady of Ethereum
The Ethereum crystal at the city's heart grants the people of Elias a resistance to cold.
Wizards are more often born near Ethereal crystals.
"As we approached the stone the air fell to black."-Royal Cartographer' Guild
Some wounded travelers may find respite in a misty copse.
The totem provides warmth during harsh winters.
What are we doing today? Oh, just watching some rocks.
I'm only thirty. No, really.
Animals are attracted to the unnatural warmth given off by fallen crystals.
Concept scenes from the Ethereal Wastes.
There was an inexplicable quiet and a far-off skeletal clicking.
Most fencers have an unspoken fear of camels.
It's just a pretty rock. I'd rather live on the beach.
Concept sketches for Early Elias.
"Behold the people of winter. My wards, my family."-Lady of Ice
The crystal of Elias serves as a waypoint for lost wanderers in the frozen lands.
Concept sketches for Decentralization
Shut your face before I put you in cold storage.
Abusing magic will eventually turn your skin weird colors.
Concept sketches for Ethereal Wastes II
It looks like hell. Smells like it too.
Touching the stone is said to bestow pyromantic mastery.
Even the air burns in those forsaken wastes.
The woods only reveal themselves to the wounded and sick.
Concept sketches for the Ethereal Forest.
More concept sketches for the Ethereal Forest.
A counterfeit totem of Elias.
He rules from the Capital. That utopia of bones.
A fortune to the wanderer who discovers this stone.
The crystal was hollowed out to build the Great Hall
column16: the center of government in Elias.

flavorText.string(): She who touches the stone assumes the title 'Lady of Fire'.
Early civilizations were often built around fallen crystals.
People would kill for what I've got.
A table full of ingredients for a helpful Happy potion.
Through the falling snow I heard a terrible gnashing. And a howl louder than anything.
A tentacled inhabitant of the Night Lands.
Settlement plans in the frozen lands are occasionally disrupted by the discovery of an ice golem nearby.
I take my time. Don't rush me or I'll take yours too.
I'm there in the mind of every man. I am arrogance and greed and offended pride.
Visit me often. I won't be dead, just still.
Best-selling author of 'Illustrations of Happy the Herbalist.'
Ice golems are mountain sized rock golems that have become frozen in place.
A mythical creature with the ability to travel through sewers and through time.
A burrowing desert creature that often ambushes merchant trains.
Monsters like these roam the desolate regions where men fear to go.
A monstrous fly-trap known for swallowing adventurers.
A former ruler of the Capital
column16: now damned to wander the spirit realms for all of time.

flavorText.string(): Through the falling snow I heard a terrible gnashing. And a howl louder than anything.
An inhabitant of the lava pools often encountered along the Pilgrim's Path.
The Puppet Master of Elias
column16: an ancient creature that 'steals' children from the city.

flavorText.string(): The lifeless skull of a former skeletal King.
"I've never seen drawings so fine associated with a face so foul."-The Capital Newspaper
Settlement plans in the frozen lands are occasionally disrupted by the discovery of an ice golem nearby.
Sometimes it pops up out of holes, sometimes it pops up out of time.
A variant of the scorpion with an acidic venom.
The ice skeleton shatters easily when attacked
column16: although very few have attempted this.

flavorText.string(): The wailing, glowing mouths lit the forest for miles in every direction.
Endlessly restless. Damnation and usurpation is the eventual fate of all skeletal kings.
A beast known for destroying houses and stealing livestock in the frozen wastes.
Stay out of its reach. It won't leave the hot spots. Still throws lava though.
The ties are more mental than physical. I believe the creature is a telepath, one that can only communicate with children.
The elite of the Capital collect the bones of exiled kings.
Happy inspired a new generation of adventurers to visit her forest.
Children of the snow peoples make a game of taunting ice golems by standing just out of reach.
The King in Yellow has an entire branch of the library dedicated to studying this creature.
Skittering sands, skittering sands. Look for the tracks, listen for the skittering.
Ice titans often live in blizzards
column16: following the storms to maintain their frigid armor.

flavorText.string(): The plants were made famous by the widespread publication of 'Illustrations of Happy the Herbalist'.
This king was exiled after failing the skeletal peoples during the Ethereal Crisis.
Princes in the frozen lands may not assume the throne without first defeating a Yeti in combat.
"It's surprisingly weak for a being made of fire."-Pilgrim Otto, a famous monk
"We're all puppets. Just some more than others."-Mayor of Elias
The skulls are cast in metal and worn as jewelry.
"I could've been your girl. And you could've been my four leaf clover." - She & Him
The town of Elias is easy to find. It's due east of old Sanford, the ice golem.
The sewer monster
column16: seen here prowling the streets of Brooklyn.

flavorText.string(): Scorpions are easily frightened  by large groups of camels.
The Lady of Ice has a personal army of ice titans for keeping peace in the frozen lands.
"They may offer you fortune and fame. Love and money and instant acclaim. But whatever they offer you, don't feed the plants." - Alan Menken
"Sleep no more! Macbeth does murder sleep!" - William Shakespeare
In between killing and eating
column16: snow yeti are also known to roll around in the snow for fun.

flavorText.string(): "Kill it with fire!"-Fire Titan
The creature's only concern is maintaining this shrine to a long dead god.
The legend of Muirhall is a popular tale about a short lived city built next to a slumbering ice golem.
Synchronization failed
column16: dropping peer. Rolled back headers count = 15.

flavorText.string(): A merkle pet that enjoys eating butterflies.
A merkle pet proficient at fending off beach crabs.
A merkle pet known to light up the shore at night.
A merkle pet used for fortune telling.
This merkle pet can generate a force field.
A merkle pet with a fiery rosette.
A merkle pet used for heating interiors.
A merkle pet with a glowing tail.
